mericas editor for the Economist, Reid suggests that much of Central and South America, though less poor, less unequal, and better educated than before, faces harder economic times now that the commodities boom of the 2000s is over. His revised, in-depth account of the region reveals dynamic societies more concerned about corruption and climate change, the uncertainties of a Donald Trump-led United States, and a political cycle that, in many cases, is turning from left-wing populism to center-right governments. This essential new edition provides important insights into the sweeping changes that have occurred in Latin America in recent years and indicates priorities for the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 0aDemocracyzLatin AmericaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Latin America / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300231700423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300231700.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles